16254b467bb8513a05fc1ce1e1920f470dc45c76de75a912935aa5804ed49e8c *bob_shared.bin



Task - 4 B
Diffie-Hellman (and its modern elliptic-curve version, ECDH) is used in TLS handshakes (HTTPS) and secure messaging apps like Signal.
It lets two parties create a shared secret over an insecure network without ever sending the key directly.
This ensures confidentiality and, when using ephemeral keys, forward secrecyâ€”past messages remain safe even if future keys are compromised.
